            "bylaw_page_end": 101
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "7",
          "text": "Building Setback/ Stepback Low-Rise Building: A low-rise building may be setback from the interior lot line. This setback may not exceed 20% of the lot frontage; Mid-Rise Building: Massing for mid-rise Buildings with a height above 13 m (42.6 ft) or the height of the streetwall, the mid-rise portion of a building shall be step-back from the interior lot lines no less than 10% of the lot frontage or 5.5m (18ft); whichever is less. Where a lot has more than one streetline, the greater lot width shall be applied.”",
